"n.泡过的食品；安慰品 【考】 sop : conciliatory / subsidy : supportive(有安慰作用的东西是 用来抚慰的/抚恤金是 用来支持的) n. 安慰剂(比如在水中浸泡过的面包片据说有安慰作用); v 浸泡 【记】源于: sip(v 吸吮)－浸泡湿润 【参】sopping(adj 浑身湿透的) 【类】sop: conciliatory = subsidy: supportive安慰剂是用来抚慰的 = 抚恤金是用来支持的sopping: dampen = frigid: cool浑身湿透的是潮湿过分 = 寒冷的是冷过分 【记】soup 汤，用来浸面包的 【相关】soap 肥皂，(浸水来洗的) sop (n.)  Old English sopp- ""bread soaked in some liquid,"" (in soppcuppe ""cup into which sops are put""), from Proto-Germanic *supp-, related to Old English verb suppan (see sup (v.2)), probably reinforced by Old French soupe (see soup (n.)). Meaning ""something given to appease"" is from 1660s, a reference to the sops given by the Sibyl to Cerberus in the ""Aeneid."" sop (v.)  Old English soppian, from the source of sop (n.). Related: Sopped; sopping."
